The idea is taken from this [post](https://leetcode.com/problems/zigzag-conversion/discuss/3465/Share-simple-C++-solution).
We re-construct the zigzag pattern into a string vector `db` by omitting all the spaces. For example,
```C++
P   A   H   N                                               db[0] PAHN
A P L S I I G   (omit all the spaces)---->                  db[1] APLSIIG
Y   I   R                                                   db[2] YIG
```
Thus, after converting the zigzag pattern into a simpler form, the only issue remainning is which row `s[i]` should lie in . We set `step` to do this.

