# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- calculate how many increments you have to do to get to the next row element 
- after calculating we found that no of jumps for rows other than the top and bottom rows is diffrent 
- So use the diffrent formula for middle rows 
- Rest is easy just keep check if the incements are in range

# :) up-Vote if it Helps
# Complexity
- Time complexity:  O(n^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string convert(string s, int numRows) {
        if (numRows == 1) return s;
        string ans = "";
        for (int i = 0; i < numRows; i++) {
            int jumps = 2 * (numRows - 1);  //no of jumps to do for reaching the next element of row
            for (int j = i; j < s.length(); j += jumps) {   // increment j always by jumps
                ans += s[j];
                int midJumps = j + jumps - 2 * i;   // jumps for middle rows 
                if (i > 0 && i < numRows - 1 && midJumps < s.length())  // check if middle jumps are in range
                    ans += s[midJumps];
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

```

