## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- If numRow=1 then we’ll return the original string.
- Else we’ll count a step variable for the first and last row. These 2 will only have one direction.

    ```
    P   | A   | H   | N
    A P | L S | I I | G
    Y   | I   | R   |
    ```

- For `s[0]=P` & `s[2]=Y` , first & last row elements we need to iterate `2 * numRows - 2` times to get the next element of this row.
- Ans for any other row we have to go `down → top` & `top → down`, s[1] to s[3] & s[3] to s[5].
- For this, we are taking a bool variable flag to access if it’s a top iteration or down.
- **Time complexity:** O(n^2).

---

## Code:

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    string convert(string s, int numRows) {
        string ans;
        if (numRows == 1) return s;

        int step = 2 * numRows - 2;

        for(int i=0; i<numRows; i++){
            if(i==0 || i==numRows-1){
                for(int j=i; j<s.size(); j+=step){
                     ans.push_back(s[j]);
                }
            }

            else{
                int j = i;
                bool flag = true;
                int step1 = 2 * (numRows - 1 - i);
                int step2 = step - step1;

                while (j < s.length()) {
                    ans.push_back(s[j]);
                    if (flag)
                        j = j + step1;
                    else
                        j = j + step2;
                    flag = !flag;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

