# Approach
I follows simple logic to iterate over the string and store the characters in a ZigZag way. 
Meaning : We will take an array of size `numRows` and we will store each characters in each of the array element by traversing the array in a top to down and vice-versa manner. 

Example : 

`string` : PAYPALISHIRING
`numRows` : 3


We will store as :
`0th Index`:PAHN
`1st Index`:APLSIIG
`2nd Index`:YIR

We will iterate over the array as : 0,1,2,1,0,1,2,1,0,1,2,......

Then by appending all the string elements, we'll get our answer.
In the program, I have used StringBuilder which is better than simple string concatenation.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public String convert(String s, int numRows) {
        StringBuilder[] arr = new StringBuilder[numRows];
        int k = 0;
        boolean mode = true;
        for(int i = 0; i < numRows; i++){
            arr[i] = new StringBuilder("");
        }
        for(int j = 0; j < s.length(); j++){
            if(mode){
                arr[k++].append(s.charAt(j));
            }
            else{
                arr[k--].append(s.charAt(j));
            }
            if(k == numRows){
                k = numRows - 2;
                mode = false;
            }
            if(k == -1){
                k = (k+2) % numRows;
                mode = true;
            }
        }
        StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder("");
        for(StringBuilder i : arr){
            ans.append(i.toString());
        }
        return ans.toString();
    }
}

```

