For row 1 and row N,  elements are at a difference of 2*(n-1) in terms of index values from the original string.
e.g for  numRows = 4 "PAYPALISHIRING"
```
0          6          12
1      5   7      11  13
2  4       8  10
3          9 
```
Above is a representation of zig zag pattern in terms of indexes in the provided string.

The difference between columns in a row which do not consist of diagonal elements form a series with a difference of **2*n-1** between each element in series.
in above example, the difference between columns which do not contain diagonal elements is:
2*(4-1) = 2*3 = 6,  e.g 
**Row 1**    0,  6(0+6),  12(6+6)
**Row 2**   1,  7(1+6),  13(7+6)
**Row 3**   2,  8(2+6)


Now for diagonal elements, the difference between each diagonal element in a row is
also the same as above , i.e 2*(n-1) 
e.g For the following diagonal series :
In **row 2** ( 5, 11 ) difference is 6.
In **row 3**  ( 4, 10 ) difference is 6.

Now we know that the difference is same for any two consecutive diagonal elements ( 5, 11 in row 2) or non-diagonal elements ( 6, 12 in row 1).

The only thing we need to calculate is the first non diagonal element (like 5 in row 2,  4 in row 3 etc.) This can be calculated by adding the following difference to the first non diagonal element in the row : 

**(The difference in Non diagonal series(i.e 0,6,12  or 1,7,13 or 2,8) ) - 2*(currentRow - 1)**

so for diagonal series in row 1 (i.e 5,11) if we just initialize this row with the first element of this series and keep on adding the diagonal series difference, we will get this series.

**So in conclusion what we have to do is :**

1) For row 1 and row N, initialize the row with element at index [row-1]
2) For other rows , initialize the row with element at index [row -1] and  element at index    [ (row-1) + {(The difference in non diagonal series(i.e 0,6,12  or 1,7,13 or 2,8) ) - 2*(currentRow - 1)} ]
3) Now we find add the series difference (2*(n-1)) alternatively to the first(non-diagonal) element and second element
e.g for row 2, initialize it with  1 and 5
			Keep on adding the difference, i.e 6 , first to 1 then to 5
			We get, 1,  5,  7(1+6), 11(5+6), 13(7+6)

4) Make checks that index dont exceed (Total length - difference)

**C++ CODE**
```
class Solution {
public:
    string convert(string s, int n) {
        if(n==1 || s.size()<=n || s.size()==1 || s.size()==2){
            return s;
        }
        int l = s.size();
        string ans = "";
        int diff = 2 * (n - 1);

        // row loop
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++)
        {
            ans.push_back(s[i - 1]);
            if (i == 1 || i == n)
            {
                int x = i - 1;
                while (x < l - diff)
                {
                    x += diff;
                    ans.push_back(s[x]);
                }
            }
            else
            {
                int new_Diff = diff - 2 * (i - 1);
                int p1 = i - 1;
                int p2 = p1 + new_Diff;
                if (p1 > l - 1 || p2 > l - 1)
                {
                    continue;
                }
                ans.push_back(s[p2]);
                bool flag = true;
                while (p2 < l - diff || p1 < l - diff)
                {
                    if (p1 < l-diff && flag == true)
                    {
                        p1 += diff;
                        ans.push_back(s[p1]);
                        flag = false;
                    }
                    if (p2 < l-diff && flag == false)
                    {
                        p2 += diff;
                        ans.push_back(s[p2]);
                        flag = true;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

