observe pattern row wise 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
from pattern we can see after every 2(n-1) elments, the next element  will come for first and last row and there is one centre element b/w 2 consecutive elements of other rows ;
so we push element row wise 
with alternate long and a short jump ;
for short jump 2*row elements decreses;
2*(n-1)-2*row; 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
