solutions.content:
Iterate through every row 
for first and last row, we need to add 2*numRows-2 to get the next element
for rows between first and last, it follows a sequence first 2*numRows-2-2*i and then 2*i is added to get the next element
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ad1880fb-d042-4f45-abcb-baebf1635d7f_1644479800.7959855.png)

```
class Solution {
    public String convert(String s, int numRows) {
        int constant = numRows - 2 + numRows;
        StringBuilder str = new StringBuilder();
        if( s.length() <= 2 || numRows == 1) return s;
        for( int i = 0 ; i  < numRows; i++ )
        {
            boolean oddTurn = false;
            for( int j = i ; j < s.length();)
            {
                str.append( s.charAt(j) );

                if( i == 0 || i == ( numRows - 1 ))
                        j += constant;
                else
                        j += ( oddTurn ? 2*i: constant-2*i );

                oddTurn =!oddTurn;    
            }
        }
        return str.toString();
    }
}
```
