solutions.content:
To: rearrange string by zigzag and read line by line

This is equivilent to: put characters with same new Row No. together in order

So we only need to get the new Row No. for each char and combine them 

Introduce a variable "up" to mark the up/down trend would be very convenient.

Tip: when `numRows == 1`, we have to return `s` else would have ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

```
public String convert(String s, int numRows) {
	if (numRows == 1) return s;
	StringBuilder[] builder = new StringBuilder[numRows + 1];
	for (int i = 0; i < builder.length; i++) builder[i] = new StringBuilder(""); 

	int row = 1, col = 1;
	boolean up = false;
	for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
		builder[row].append(c);
		if (row == numRows) up = true; // we need to change direction to go up
		if (row == 1) up = false; // we need to change direction to go down
		if (up) {
			row--;
			col++;
		} else {
			row++;
		}
	}

	String res = "";
	for (int i = 1; i < builder.length; i++) res += new String(builder[i]);
	return res;
}
```

